In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a big
pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until
rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Halve, core, and finely dice half the
@Bell Pepper{1}; thinly slice remaining bell pepper into strips. Drain
@Mango{4%oz}, reserving juice. Halve, peel, and finely dice @Yellow Onion{1}(diced).
Mince some of the diced onion until you have 2 TBSP; set aside for step 5.
Dice @Tomato{1}. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add diced bell pepper and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add mango and cook, stirring
occasionally, until lightly charred, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Add ¼ cup water and @Sugar{1/2%tsp}; cook until liquid has mostly evaporated,
~{30%seconds}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a medium #bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium high-heat. Add diced onion and
sliced bell pepper; season with salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
softened and lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @Ground Pork{10%oz}, @Mexican Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, salt (we used
½ tsp), and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and
cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir in reserved mango juice and cook until
thickened, ~{30%seconds}. Remove from heat. Taste and season with salt and
pepper.

> Ground pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

To bowl with mango mixture, add tomato, minced onion, juice from one lime
(juice from 1 1/2 limes for 4 servings; add a bit more if desired), and a large
drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon}; stir to combine. Taste and season generously
with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with pork, salsa, and @Guacamole{4%tablespoon}
in separate sections. Serve.